  "units": "degrees Fahrenheit",
  "point_in_time_rule": "known_from_ts = epoch( (local target-day 23:00) - 24*lead hours ). Open-Meteo docs: temperature_2m_previous_dayN is 'the value predicted 24*N hours before valid time'. The day-D max can fall on any hour up to 23:00 local, whose forecast was issued ~24*N h earlier; anchoring at the LAST hour guarantees no contributing hour was issued after known_from_ts (leakage-safe maximum issue time). Verified empirically that this lands inside the Kalshi quote window for lead1 (~13h after open) and before the open for lead2.",
